\f0 Description: A Thief 2 Fan Mission  \par
                       This is the sequel to "A Friend In Need."\par
                       It's not necessary to play AFIN first but it is recommended.\par
\b0\par
\par
\b Briefing:  You've broken into the law offices of Dewey, Cheatem & Howe in order\par
                  to discover the location of Lord Bafford's new summer residence.  Now that\par
                  you have it, it's time to pay the place a visit.  It's really an unnecessary risk\par
                  as you don't need the money...but hey...it's another chance to piss off\par
                  Lord Bafford!\par
\par
                  No sense in waiting...It's time to begin.\i  \par
\par
\i0\par
Note From SlyFoxx:  If you cause a lot of commotion in certain locations and/or knock out \par
                                      certain AI, you'll be missing out on key bits of information.  So if you \par
                                      plan to run around like this is Unreal Tournament don't be surprised if \par
                                      you get surprised or can't find most of the loot!  That said, there are things\par
                                      in this mission that you can only experience if you are a bloodthirsty taffer\par
                                      who likes to slice people up! \par
\par
                                     If you get up in the guard towers and look back towards the main house\par
                                     you'll be getting a view that will test the limits of the game engine.  I have\par
                                     experienced no crashes but do suggest a quick save before doing so.\par
\par
                                     There are some AI conversations in this mission.  They are triggered by\par
                                     something called a Bounds Trigger.  The trigger is destroyed \i almost \i0\par
                                     immediatly after it does its thing so the conversation only plays once.\par
                                     What that means to you is that if you keep moving while inside the\par
                                     trigger area before it gets destroyed the conversation will keep starting\par
                                     over.  So if you just hold still for a few seconds everything will be good.\par
\par
                                     As is often the case the pick pocket stats at the end of the mission are\par
                                     incorrect.  The correct total is 9.\par
\par
                                    This mission is not very difficult.  It's not supposed to be.  It almost didn't\par
                                    get finished but I had promised a sequel to "A Friend In Need" and I do\par
                                    my best to keep my promises.  It also served as a learning experience as to\par
                                    how to implement more "fancy DromEd stuff."  So though the game-play\par
                                    is on the easy side this is by far the most complex and challenging mission\par
                                    I have ever released from a design standpoint.  \par
\par
